<h2 style="text-align:center">Welcome to RoR Ecommerce!</h2>

<% if @password %>
  <p> Welcome, You are the Super Admin user. </p>
  <p>Your email and login is: <%= @user.email %> </p>
  <p>Your password is: <%= @password %> </p>
  <p>PLEASE WRITE THIS INFORMATION DOWN.</p>
<% end %>

<% if @no_roles %>
  <p>
    <b>You need to run rake db:seed</b>
  </p>
<% else %>
  <ol>
    <li>It would be best to go to <%= link_to 'Admin Users', admin_users_path, 'data-popup' => true %> and change your password and email to something more personal.</li>
    <li>Go to <%= link_to 'Config', admin_config_overviews_path, 'data-popup' => true %> and click on every option in the sub-header.</li>
    <li>Then create <%= link_to 'Properties', admin_merchandise_properties_path, 'data-popup' => true %>.  A property is just a characteristic that your products have.</li>
    <li>Add <%= link_to 'Product Type', admin_merchandise_product_types_path, 'data-popup' => true %></li>
    <li>Next create a <%= link_to 'Prototype', admin_merchandise_prototypes_path, 'data-popup' => true %>.  A prototype is the building block of a product.  The prototype is used to inherit the types of properties that your products will have.</li>
    <li>You should create a shipping category by going to <%= link_to 'Shipping Categories', admin_config_shipping_categories_path, 'data-popup' => true %>.</li>
    <li>Next create a <%= link_to 'Product', admin_merchandise_products_path, 'data-popup' => true %></li>
    <li>Next create a Variant.  A variant is a specific type of product.  If Diet Gatorade is your product, Fruit Punch Gatorage might be your variant. To
      do this click to edit your product and then click add variant.</li>
    <li>Next you need to upload Images.  To do this click to edit your product and then click add image.</li>
    <li>You need inventory .  To do this click <%= link_to 'Inventory', admin_inventory_overviews_path, 'data-popup' => true %>.  Then click purchase order and follow the step to create a purchase order.  Once the purchase order is complete, you need to click receive for the inventory to be in stock.
    </li>
  </ol>
<% end %>